WEBVTT

00:16.850 --> 00:18.852
[heavy breathing]

00:39.914 --> 00:40.749
[grunts]

00:41.458 --> 00:42.834
-Time!
-[stopwatch beeps]

00:43.668 --> 00:44.669
Holy shit.

00:45.962 --> 00:47.172
-What is it?
-Guess.

00:49.132 --> 00:50.133
5:19?

00:50.717 --> 00:51.593
5:07.

00:53.303 --> 00:54.846
That's enough for Ridgewood?

00:54.929 --> 00:57.140
Yeah. That's almost enough
for the Olympics.

00:58.558 --> 00:59.934
Let's get you some dinner.

01:01.144 --> 01:02.729
-5:07
-Yeah, man.

01:07.108 --> 01:08.568
[door opens]

01:09.569 --> 01:10.403
Woo.

01:11.279 --> 01:12.697
Hey, how was it?

01:12.781 --> 01:15.408
We are in the presence
of a future Olympian.

01:16.910 --> 01:18.119
Just guess my time.

01:18.203 --> 01:19.913
Okay. Five...

01:19.996 --> 01:21.539
-5:07.
-What?

01:21.623 --> 01:24.042
-5:07.
-5:07? That's incredible.

01:24.417 --> 01:26.044
-Right?
-That's my best.

01:26.169 --> 01:27.879
We made that.
Did you know we made you?

01:28.004 --> 01:29.631
-Okay.
-We made you with our bodies.

01:29.714 --> 01:31.132
-I know.
-Okay.

01:31.257 --> 01:33.927
Go take a shower.
I'm making breakfast for dinner.

01:54.364 --> 01:55.490
[sniffs]

02:05.625 --> 02:06.459
[grunts]

02:07.335 --> 02:09.003
Oh, fuck. [exhales]

02:11.047 --> 02:14.092
-It won't change until you talk to Jim.
-I gotta catch him on a good day.

02:14.175 --> 02:17.137
-He's in a bad mood.
-Yeah, he's always in a bad mood, Brian.

02:17.220 --> 02:20.223
-You just have to sit him down.
-Okay, I hear you, all right?

02:20.306 --> 02:22.267
Brian, I'm looking for work too, but--

02:22.350 --> 02:23.184
[clears throat]

02:23.268 --> 02:24.435
-There he is.
-Hey.

02:24.519 --> 02:27.480
-I'm gonna go get some eggs. Wanna come?
-Sure.

02:27.605 --> 02:29.774
Hey, get milk, too, okay?

02:32.277 --> 02:33.278
["Rip Van Winkle" playing]

02:33.361 --> 02:35.363
♪ You're sleeping all your moments away ♪

02:35.446 --> 02:37.615
♪ I'm counting every breath
That you take ♪

02:38.241 --> 02:41.828
♪ You've been snoozing 20 years
And lengthening... ♪

02:41.911 --> 02:43.163
-God.
-Right?

02:43.246 --> 02:45.123
-Yeah. It's fucking great.
-Yeah, I'm obsessed.

02:45.206 --> 02:46.040
[laughs]

02:46.583 --> 02:47.792
All right. I'm going in.

02:48.293 --> 02:49.919
You staying? Or are you going?

02:50.003 --> 02:51.296
-I'm staying.
-Okay.

02:51.379 --> 02:55.341
♪ ...have given up for good ♪

02:55.425 --> 02:56.634
♪ You say, "Hey" ♪

02:56.718 --> 02:58.636
Hey. Can you bring me something?

02:59.095 --> 03:00.388
I'll think about it.

03:01.097 --> 03:02.390
♪ I said, "Hey" ♪

03:03.766 --> 03:06.227
♪ "I'm all right" ♪

03:07.103 --> 03:09.189
♪ Every time I turn around ♪

03:10.315 --> 03:11.149
[door chimes]

03:11.232 --> 03:12.650
-Hey, Tommy.
-Hey, man.

03:15.528 --> 03:16.946
[humming]

03:22.952 --> 03:25.079
♪ You can spot a hawk a mile away ♪

03:26.039 --> 03:28.082
♪ Cursing all those old blue jays ♪

03:28.666 --> 03:31.002
♪ But every time I turn around ♪

03:31.085 --> 03:33.630
♪ And have given up for good ♪

03:33.713 --> 03:34.964
[tires squeal]

03:35.048 --> 03:35.882
No!

03:52.440 --> 03:53.983
[indistinct chatter]

03:59.447 --> 04:01.783
I guess the driver had a heart attack.

04:02.116 --> 04:03.493
-It's awful.
-Yes.

04:06.704 --> 04:07.872
[knocking on door]

04:09.499 --> 04:10.375
[Naomi] Logan?

04:14.128 --> 04:14.963
Yeah?

04:19.801 --> 04:21.052
The Kellmans are leaving.

04:25.265 --> 04:26.099
Okay.

04:40.363 --> 04:41.823
Are you guys gonna stay here?

04:45.743 --> 04:47.036
I can't afford the rent.

04:47.912 --> 04:49.330
With me being out of work and now...

04:50.999 --> 04:53.376
You should stay at our mountain house.

04:54.877 --> 04:57.547
-No.
-No, I'm serious, Naomi.

04:57.672 --> 04:59.632
I mean, it's just sitting there, and...

05:00.049 --> 05:02.176
You know that Bruce won't have
a problem with it.

05:03.219 --> 05:04.262
I want to help.

05:07.098 --> 05:08.558
I thought you guys were selling...

05:09.225 --> 05:10.810
We are, but...

05:11.561 --> 05:14.772
You just have to leave for a bit
on Sundays during open houses.

05:18.234 --> 05:20.194
-It's nothing.
-I don't know, Ally.

05:20.278 --> 05:22.905
-Having people living there is not--
-It'll be fine.

05:23.948 --> 05:26.743
Okay? You can look after the place.

05:28.244 --> 05:31.456
Logan would kill me if I pulled him
out of school right now.

05:32.040 --> 05:34.917
Okay, look, it's just until 
you get back on your feet.

05:35.001 --> 05:36.544
And you'll come back.

05:39.422 --> 05:40.548
I just can't believe it.

05:41.466 --> 05:42.342
He's dead.

05:58.941 --> 06:00.193
Okay.

06:02.487 --> 06:03.363
[sighs]

06:03.821 --> 06:04.655
Ready?

06:04.739 --> 06:05.698
[sighs]

06:06.866 --> 06:07.700
Yep.

06:13.998 --> 06:15.208
[engine turns over]

06:48.991 --> 06:52.245
No, you're not listening 
to what I'm saying.

06:53.204 --> 06:54.831
I am the executor.

06:57.583 --> 07:00.378
Well, yes. He was my husband.

07:02.797 --> 07:03.631
What?

07:06.008 --> 07:06.884
Hello?

07:07.218 --> 07:08.094
Hello?

07:08.386 --> 07:09.679
Can you hear me?

07:10.847 --> 07:11.722
Hello?

07:12.473 --> 07:13.307
[phone thuds]

07:14.058 --> 07:14.976
Damn it.

07:15.810 --> 07:16.644
[sighs]

07:21.190 --> 07:23.192
[instrumental music plays over radio]

07:29.657 --> 07:30.741
[turns off radio]

07:31.993 --> 07:33.870
How long did you say 
we were gonna be here for?

07:33.953 --> 07:36.831
-I don't know, Logan.
-You said I'd be back before graduation.

07:36.914 --> 07:40.209
I said I don't know,
and I'm gonna do my best, okay?

07:43.796 --> 07:44.881
[Naomi sighs]

07:48.509 --> 07:51.345
Can you pass me my phone?
It's at your feet.

07:56.184 --> 07:57.310
[grunts]

08:00.855 --> 08:02.064
Hey, Mom! Shit!

08:02.148 --> 08:03.816
[tires squeal]

08:03.900 --> 08:06.402
Oh, sh--! Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

08:06.486 --> 08:08.279
Please tell me he's okay.

08:08.362 --> 08:10.239
[breathing heavily]

08:11.199 --> 08:12.617
He's-- he's not there.

08:13.951 --> 08:14.785
What?

08:26.964 --> 08:28.591
Hey, let's just-- let's just go.

08:29.467 --> 08:30.343
What?

08:31.469 --> 08:32.720
I could have killed him.

08:33.179 --> 08:34.347
[panting]

08:35.723 --> 08:36.933
Mom, your nose.

08:38.518 --> 08:39.393
Oh, shit.

08:39.477 --> 08:40.394
Hey, uh...

08:41.437 --> 08:42.396
Here.

08:43.606 --> 08:44.482
Here.

08:44.941 --> 08:46.400
It's just the altitude.

09:39.996 --> 09:41.163
Oh, shit.

09:41.622 --> 09:44.000
-Sorry.
-[laughing] Oh, no worry at all, honey.

09:44.083 --> 09:45.084
Wait a minute.

09:45.668 --> 09:47.920
You must be Logan.

09:48.504 --> 09:49.463
Hi?

09:49.755 --> 09:51.924
Oh, and hold on...

09:52.008 --> 09:52.883
Naomi.

09:53.384 --> 09:57.096
-I'm sorry?
-Oh, forgive me. I'm Martha.

09:57.847 --> 09:59.307
Bruce and Allison's neighbor.

09:59.390 --> 10:02.018
She told me her sister and nephew
were coming in.

10:02.101 --> 10:05.980
She emailed me a picture,
so I knew exactly who you two were.

10:06.063 --> 10:07.356
Oh, okay.

10:09.108 --> 10:11.569
So sorry for what happened
to your husband.

10:12.278 --> 10:14.280
Allison told me all about it.

10:14.697 --> 10:16.240
So gruesome.

10:16.949 --> 10:18.534
You must miss him dearly.

10:19.076 --> 10:20.578
Yeah, we-- we do.

10:21.370 --> 10:23.789
I lost my husband a few years back.

10:24.206 --> 10:27.418
Not a day goes by 
that I don't feel the void.

10:28.502 --> 10:30.963
-Mom, should we--
-Oh. Oh, yes.

10:31.172 --> 10:33.341
I won't keep you any longer. 
If you need anything,

10:33.424 --> 10:35.843
my house is just west through
the woods. You can't miss it.

10:35.926 --> 10:37.845
Thank you. [clears throat]
It's very kind of you.

10:37.928 --> 10:40.389
It's always nice to know
you have someone nearby.

10:41.098 --> 10:43.517
The quiet out here can get real loud.

10:44.935 --> 10:45.936
Buh-bye now.

10:58.407 --> 10:59.408
[Naomi] You okay?

11:00.910 --> 11:01.786
Yeah.

11:05.581 --> 11:07.124
[engine turns over]

11:33.693 --> 11:35.277
Oh. Whoa.

11:35.361 --> 11:36.195
[Naomi] Yeah.

11:37.655 --> 11:41.450
Leave it to Ally to have 
the biggest house on the mountain.

11:45.371 --> 11:47.790
How have we never been here before?
It's fucking huge.

11:47.915 --> 11:48.916
Language.

11:51.001 --> 11:51.961
[sighs]

11:52.044 --> 11:52.920
But yeah.

11:54.088 --> 11:55.548
It is huge.

11:56.340 --> 11:57.842
Okay. Let's go.

12:26.579 --> 12:27.455
Well...

12:30.541 --> 12:31.959
Home sweet home.

12:44.555 --> 12:46.557
[telephone ringing]

12:56.192 --> 12:57.026
Hello?

12:59.028 --> 13:00.446
Uh, yes.

13:01.405 --> 13:02.573
Just got in.

13:04.950 --> 13:06.160
Oh, okay.

13:06.243 --> 13:07.077
[chuckles]

13:07.703 --> 13:08.621
Thanks.

13:11.457 --> 13:12.875
Who was that?

13:12.958 --> 13:13.959
Martha...

13:14.418 --> 13:15.461
the neighbor.

13:15.711 --> 13:16.545
Just...

13:16.921 --> 13:18.923
calling to see if we got in okay.

13:19.006 --> 13:20.716
[cell phone ringing]

13:20.800 --> 13:23.302
I was kind of hoping 
I wouldn't have reception up here.

13:24.929 --> 13:25.763
Hello?

13:26.889 --> 13:27.723
Oh.

13:28.516 --> 13:29.350
Hi.

13:30.351 --> 13:31.352
Oh, no, no.

13:32.436 --> 13:33.437
Well, you know...

13:34.063 --> 13:36.232
we've been driving all night, so...

13:40.319 --> 13:41.237
[Naomi sighs]

13:41.695 --> 13:43.197
But, yeah...

13:43.280 --> 13:44.448
Yeah, I know.

13:45.533 --> 13:46.492
He's okay.

13:47.284 --> 13:48.160
I know.

13:49.411 --> 13:51.247
We're at my sister's house.

13:52.498 --> 13:55.167
It's a big, nice house.

13:55.668 --> 13:56.919
I think he likes it.

14:00.130 --> 14:02.091
[Naomi continues speaking indistinctly]

14:13.394 --> 14:14.395
[sighs]

15:08.532 --> 15:09.575
[hinge squeaks]

15:09.658 --> 15:10.492
[door thuds]

15:14.872 --> 15:15.956
[light switch clicks]

15:34.433 --> 15:35.351
[stairs creak]

16:59.935 --> 17:01.228
[exhales]

17:03.981 --> 17:04.940
[yelps]

17:05.024 --> 17:06.567
[breathing heavily]

17:09.236 --> 17:10.112
Jesus.

17:34.094 --> 17:34.970
Logan?

17:36.305 --> 17:37.139
Yeah?

17:37.681 --> 17:39.183
Did you get a chance to sleep today?

17:40.559 --> 17:41.935
Not-- not really.

17:42.227 --> 17:44.563
Well, you'll sleep like a rock tonight.

17:46.648 --> 17:48.442
First open house is tomorrow,

17:48.525 --> 17:50.819
so we gotta be out of here by 11:00, okay?

17:52.571 --> 17:53.405
Okay.

17:54.156 --> 17:57.076
Honey, are you sure you don't want to keep
that stuff in my room?

17:57.159 --> 17:58.160
No, no, it's okay.

17:59.870 --> 18:00.704
Okay.

18:01.872 --> 18:03.207
Well, I'm gonna head to bed.

18:05.167 --> 18:06.001
Love you.

18:20.474 --> 18:21.767
[clock ticking]

18:50.921 --> 18:54.007
[knocking at door]

19:04.643 --> 19:06.103
[car engine idles]

19:31.587 --> 19:33.881
[honking]

19:35.048 --> 19:36.383
[car drives away]

20:32.648 --> 20:33.732
Who are you?

20:34.775 --> 20:36.735
What are you doing on our property?

20:37.319 --> 20:38.153
Ma'am?

20:39.196 --> 20:40.530
What do you want?

20:42.074 --> 20:43.867
Ma'am, this is our house.

20:44.743 --> 20:46.370
-Do you need help?
-No!

20:46.453 --> 20:47.496
Oh, God!

20:48.080 --> 20:49.915
[cries in distress]

22:05.574 --> 22:06.950
[inhales]

22:07.367 --> 22:09.786
[exhales]

22:13.999 --> 22:17.461
You need to get up right now.
The open house is starting in 15 minutes.

22:17.544 --> 22:20.422
Ed, come on. You gotta get 
the sign-in sheet out of the car.

22:20.505 --> 22:23.175
-You kidding me?
-The open house ends at five.

22:23.258 --> 22:25.010
Ed is gonna be running the show today,

22:25.093 --> 22:28.221
which means he will turn off 
all the lights, he'll lock up.

22:28.305 --> 22:31.183
And Ed, don't forget 
to leave the key under the mat.

22:31.266 --> 22:32.142
Got it.

22:32.434 --> 22:34.102
Oh, okay.

22:34.186 --> 22:36.104
-And do I need to do--
-Oh, God, no, no.

22:36.188 --> 22:38.607
You don't have to do a thing,
except one:

22:38.690 --> 22:41.777
Do not come back here until after five,

22:41.860 --> 22:46.031
because we do not want to upset 
any potential buyers.

22:46.114 --> 22:48.408
-Mom, why didn't you wake me up?
-Oh, sorry.

22:48.492 --> 22:51.119
-I got a call and then I didn't--
-They scared the hell out of me.

22:51.203 --> 22:52.579
Ed, make his bed.

22:55.499 --> 22:58.919
You two really have to get going.
Really. Now.

23:13.517 --> 23:14.643
[doorbell rings]

23:19.773 --> 23:21.149
Hey, hey. No, hey.

23:26.196 --> 23:27.239
Welcome.

23:27.322 --> 23:30.450
And if you have any further questions
today, just sign in right there,

23:30.534 --> 23:33.161
and otherwise,
take a cookie, look around,

23:33.245 --> 23:34.788
and, uh, I'm here to help.

23:50.303 --> 23:52.556
[Naomi] So, why would she knock?

23:53.306 --> 23:54.391
She's nuts.

23:55.142 --> 23:56.601
Maybe she was lost.

23:58.770 --> 24:01.356
I just don't think the people up here
know what privacy is.

24:01.898 --> 24:05.277
Excuse me? Your card was declined.
Do you have another one we could use?

24:06.653 --> 24:07.529
Oh.

24:08.989 --> 24:10.157
Uh, you know what?

24:10.699 --> 24:11.867
I'll just use cash.

24:12.242 --> 24:13.118
Okay.

24:19.207 --> 24:20.125
Here. I-I got it.

24:20.208 --> 24:21.751
No. Honey, you don't even--

24:26.590 --> 24:27.799
It's birthday money.

24:29.217 --> 24:31.678
-Uh, here you go. No change.
-Thanks.

24:33.346 --> 24:34.222
[clears throat]

24:36.349 --> 24:37.893
Where'd you get birthday money?

24:38.727 --> 24:39.811
Aunt Allison.

24:42.397 --> 24:43.398
It's okay.

24:48.028 --> 24:48.945
Thank you.

24:55.869 --> 24:56.786
[sighs]

24:58.330 --> 25:00.790
You know what?
Let's play a game.

25:01.416 --> 25:03.460
-What?
-Yeah. Come on, it'll be fun.

25:03.543 --> 25:05.462
Uh, if you won the lottery...

25:06.963 --> 25:08.798
what would you do with the winnings?

25:09.925 --> 25:11.092
I don't wanna play.

25:12.511 --> 25:13.595
Come on.

25:14.638 --> 25:15.639
Amuse me.

25:16.515 --> 25:17.557
Fine. Uh...

25:18.350 --> 25:19.226
I'd...

25:20.352 --> 25:21.811
I'd pay off our debt.

25:23.688 --> 25:24.523
Okay.

25:24.606 --> 25:25.982
We're not that bad off.

25:26.983 --> 25:28.193
But I would let you.

25:30.987 --> 25:32.822
I'd buy us a new house back home.

25:34.491 --> 25:36.201
-Can we have a pool?
-And a track.

25:37.744 --> 25:39.996
I'd go to the Olympics in Japan.

25:40.664 --> 25:42.791
-Can I come with you?
-Yeah. First class.

25:43.208 --> 25:45.752
Other than that, I'd probably 
just give the rest to you.

25:47.462 --> 25:48.296
No.

25:49.172 --> 25:50.382
I don't need it. You...

25:52.384 --> 25:54.761
You'd probably spend it 
on things that matter.

25:56.888 --> 25:58.598
Well, I personally think that...

26:01.059 --> 26:03.019
your dream of going to the Olympics

26:03.103 --> 26:05.939
and owning a home 
with the biggest backyard ever

26:07.023 --> 26:08.650
are things that matter.

26:10.026 --> 26:10.944
Thanks.

26:12.237 --> 26:13.655
Okay. My turn.

26:14.698 --> 26:15.782
Debt.

26:18.368 --> 26:19.869
And then I think I would...

26:20.704 --> 26:22.330
start doing photography again.

26:22.706 --> 26:25.625
-Really?
-Yeah. I think so. I used to love it.

26:28.295 --> 26:29.671
You should...

26:30.547 --> 26:32.007
You should start again now.

26:33.008 --> 26:34.259
-Please.
-You should.

26:34.342 --> 26:36.636
You don't have to win the lottery 
to do that.

26:37.512 --> 26:38.930
Now you sound like your dad.

26:40.056 --> 26:41.349
["Jingle Bells" playing]

26:41.433 --> 26:43.059
♪ Dashing through the snow ♪

26:43.143 --> 26:47.022
♪ In a one-horse open sleigh ♪

26:47.105 --> 26:50.567
♪ Over the fields we go ♪

26:50.650 --> 26:53.653
♪ Laughing all the way... ♪

26:55.655 --> 26:57.490
[man] I don't think I've seen you before.

26:57.574 --> 27:00.452
[Naomi] Oh. Oh, yeah.
We've been getting a lot of that.

27:00.535 --> 27:01.578
[man] Oh, yeah.

27:01.661 --> 27:03.997
Everybody knows everybody 
in these small towns, huh?

27:04.497 --> 27:06.791
Mm-hmm. I have noticed.

27:07.709 --> 27:09.377
It's good to see some new faces.

27:10.045 --> 27:11.838
-Especially pretty ones.
-[Naomi laughs]

27:11.921 --> 27:14.382
I just mean the mountain folk
can get a little, uh...

27:14.466 --> 27:17.427
scruffy at times,
and I am not talking about the men.

27:19.971 --> 27:21.056
Whereabouts are you from?

27:21.765 --> 27:24.601
-Uh, well, we're from California.
-Mom, can we go?

27:24.684 --> 27:26.436
Hey, buddy. How you doing?

27:29.230 --> 27:30.315
Mom?

27:32.192 --> 27:34.694
-Uh, I'm so sorry.
-No.

27:55.340 --> 27:56.758
You didn't have to be rude.

27:59.052 --> 28:00.261
[exhales]

28:00.804 --> 28:02.138
You were flirting.

28:03.223 --> 28:04.140
Logan...

28:05.475 --> 28:08.061
He was just talking to me.
I was being friendly.

28:12.524 --> 28:13.817
Are we allowed to go in yet?

28:15.485 --> 28:16.361
Yeah.

28:16.945 --> 28:18.446
Said it was over at five.

28:33.420 --> 28:36.172
-[Logan] There's no key.
-[Naomi] What? Is it unlocked?

28:41.803 --> 28:42.679
Hello?

28:45.890 --> 28:46.891
[door closes]

29:06.119 --> 29:07.203
Oh, Jesus!

29:07.662 --> 29:09.205
-Oh!
-Did you not-- did you not hear us?

29:09.289 --> 29:11.416
Sorry. I was just locking everything up.

29:11.499 --> 29:12.625
We ran long.

29:12.709 --> 29:15.295
Uh, Jonie's picking me up right now,
so I, uh...

29:15.378 --> 29:18.339
I'm rushing, but your keys--
I left them right there,

29:18.423 --> 29:20.759
and, um, that should be everything.

29:21.301 --> 29:24.429
Okay? So, um... have-- have a great night.

29:25.722 --> 29:26.598
Thank you.

29:33.313 --> 29:34.481
Turn on the light.

29:40.403 --> 29:41.321
Mom.

29:42.280 --> 29:45.492
Have you ever thought about
how, like, weird open houses are?

29:45.825 --> 29:46.659
What?

29:48.036 --> 29:50.747
I mean, you give your keys
to someone you hardly know,

29:51.247 --> 29:54.542
they stand in one room and welcome in 
a bunch of complete strangers,

29:54.626 --> 29:57.504
and those people
just roam around the house.

29:58.004 --> 30:00.423
And the realtor doesn't check the house
when it's done, right?

30:00.507 --> 30:03.009
They just... turn the lights off and go?

30:03.843 --> 30:06.763
Okay, well, now I'm not 
gonna sleep tonight.

30:10.350 --> 30:12.060
Maybe you shouldn't sleep tonight.

30:13.228 --> 30:14.187
Stop.

30:29.786 --> 30:31.955
[inhales, exhales]

30:45.844 --> 30:48.346
[Man on TV]
But a suicide generally leaves a note.

30:48.429 --> 30:51.349
[Man 2]  Well, this one didn't.
Probably didn't have time.

30:51.432 --> 30:52.392
[pauses movie]

30:53.226 --> 30:54.143
I have to pee.

30:55.228 --> 30:56.062
Okay.

30:58.731 --> 30:59.941
[exhales]

31:16.291 --> 31:18.585
[door squeaks]

31:30.013 --> 31:31.389
[sighs]

31:35.101 --> 31:37.228
[telephone ringing]

31:42.358 --> 31:43.610
Just gonna watch it ring?

31:46.154 --> 31:46.988
Hello?

31:49.115 --> 31:49.949
Hello?

31:51.701 --> 31:52.702
Who is it?

31:53.828 --> 31:54.662
It--

31:55.079 --> 31:56.122
Can you hear me?

31:56.205 --> 31:57.415
Is anyone there?

32:01.920 --> 32:03.546
-What?
-It's just us.

32:03.630 --> 32:05.298
Like, I could just hear echoing.

32:14.515 --> 32:16.893
[Man 2 on TV]  Or they might have been
in South America...

32:16.976 --> 32:18.102
[TV continues indistinctly]

32:18.186 --> 32:19.520
[shower running]

33:27.880 --> 33:29.549
Hey, Mom, have you seen my phone?

33:30.008 --> 33:32.760
Uh... no. Sorry, babe.

33:33.094 --> 33:33.928
I haven't.

33:35.388 --> 33:36.973
I'm gonna use yours real quick.

33:37.306 --> 33:38.141
Okay.

34:17.138 --> 34:18.973
[loud thudding]

34:34.572 --> 34:36.783
[grinding noise]

34:56.511 --> 34:57.762
[thud]

34:58.554 --> 34:59.472
[Naomi screams]

35:02.975 --> 35:05.061
-Logan!
-Oh, shoot! Sorry, Mom. God.

35:06.729 --> 35:07.939
You scared me.

35:08.022 --> 35:10.733
The water is ice cold.
I have to go check the tank.

35:10.817 --> 35:12.985
-Wait, that's in the basement.
-I know.

35:13.778 --> 35:17.490
-I heard something banging down there.
-Yeah, it's probably the old pipes.

35:30.378 --> 35:32.004
[stairs creak]

36:06.455 --> 36:08.708
[flashlight clicks off, thuds down]

36:21.470 --> 36:22.680
Oh, come on.

36:29.604 --> 36:30.980
[match strikes]

36:33.649 --> 36:34.734
Ugh.

36:34.817 --> 36:35.860
Jesus.

36:35.943 --> 36:36.819
Okay.

36:36.903 --> 36:37.778
[exhales]

36:52.126 --> 36:53.169
[door slams shut]

36:54.253 --> 36:55.129
Logan?

37:03.262 --> 37:04.347
Logan?

37:08.726 --> 37:10.186
That's not funny, Logan.

37:10.269 --> 37:12.688
-What?
-You slammed the basement door on me.

37:13.564 --> 37:15.441
I have no idea what you're talking about.

37:21.989 --> 37:22.949
[sighs]

37:25.076 --> 37:26.327
Maybe the door is broken.

37:43.678 --> 37:44.971
[breathing heavily]

37:57.233 --> 37:58.734
-Time! [exhales]
-[stopwatch beeps]

37:58.818 --> 38:00.319
5:34.

38:01.195 --> 38:03.197
-Nice.
-It needs to be faster.

38:03.281 --> 38:05.032
What? That's great.

38:05.116 --> 38:08.202
No. Come on, you don't get it.
It needs to be faster.

38:08.286 --> 38:12.248
Honey, you're on a mountain.
Maybe you ran more than a mile.

38:12.331 --> 38:14.417
No, I mapped it out.

38:15.418 --> 38:17.461
Are you sure you started 
the second I left?

38:18.754 --> 38:20.506
You can do it yourself if you want.

38:30.808 --> 38:32.226
Did you find your phone yet?

38:33.269 --> 38:35.521
No, it's gone.

38:35.938 --> 38:38.482
Well, it's not gone.
It has to be somewhere.

38:39.859 --> 38:41.527
-I don't know.
-Who's that?

38:52.079 --> 38:52.913
Hey.

38:53.956 --> 38:54.790
Hey.

38:55.916 --> 38:56.751
Oh...

38:57.460 --> 38:58.461
It's you guys.

38:59.337 --> 39:01.339
-What are you doing here?
-Right.

39:01.839 --> 39:02.882
This looks bad.

39:03.174 --> 39:05.885
I was just on the back roads,
saw the "For Sale" sign.

39:07.053 --> 39:08.429
[clears throat] Honey.

39:09.096 --> 39:09.972
Logan.

39:11.140 --> 39:12.099
[door closes]

39:13.934 --> 39:15.895
I'm sorry. He's, uh...

39:15.978 --> 39:18.272
No, no need to apologize. I can relate.

39:18.898 --> 39:22.401
-You have teenagers?
-No, but I was one once.

39:23.736 --> 39:27.073
Well, this is my sister's house.
We're just staying here for a bit.

39:27.156 --> 39:28.032
Lucky us.

39:28.616 --> 39:31.077
Yeah. Um, you could call the realtors.

39:31.660 --> 39:33.579
They're the ones that set up the showings.

39:33.662 --> 39:35.414
Got it. Thank you.

39:35.998 --> 39:36.874
I'll do that.

39:39.877 --> 39:40.836
You know what?

39:42.046 --> 39:43.255
While we're here...

39:43.756 --> 39:46.133
would there be any way at all 
I can just peek inside?

39:54.433 --> 39:56.560
-So you looking to move?
-Thinking about it.

39:57.895 --> 39:59.772
I'd kill for this kind of privacy.

40:02.400 --> 40:03.901
I don't think I caught your name.

40:03.984 --> 40:05.027
Uh, Naomi.

40:05.111 --> 40:07.571
Naomi. It's nice to meet you. I'm Chris.

40:08.030 --> 40:11.575
Well, I'll let you do your thing.
Don't mind me.

40:12.034 --> 40:12.910
Great.

40:15.162 --> 40:16.580
[keys clacking]

40:26.590 --> 40:28.592
[presses key, "Rip Van Winkle" plays]

40:32.805 --> 40:35.182
♪ You're sleeping all your moments away ♪

41:01.792 --> 41:03.627
[door creaks open]

41:03.711 --> 41:05.880
♪ I'm counting every breath
That you take ♪

41:06.338 --> 41:08.966
♪ You've been snoozing 20 years ♪

41:16.557 --> 41:17.516
No!

41:22.229 --> 41:23.063
Chris?

41:24.940 --> 41:25.774
Hello?

41:30.863 --> 41:32.114
Who are you talking to?

41:32.198 --> 41:33.866
Um, that guy...

41:33.949 --> 41:36.535
wanted to see the house 
since he missed yesterday.

41:37.536 --> 41:38.829
He's still here?

41:38.913 --> 41:41.957
He's probably left.
He was just looking around.

41:42.541 --> 41:44.084
I was in my room.

41:44.168 --> 41:45.711
[turns faucet on, off]

41:48.130 --> 41:49.006
Logan?

41:50.883 --> 41:51.800
[sighs]

42:14.698 --> 42:15.866
[blows air]

42:27.461 --> 42:28.629
[camera shutter clicks]

42:40.474 --> 42:41.559
[camera shutter clicks]

42:47.731 --> 42:48.732
[exhales]

43:23.809 --> 43:25.269
Okay. [exhales]

43:26.437 --> 43:29.481
What do you want to have 
with your mac and cheese?

43:30.232 --> 43:31.692
Hot dogs?

43:31.775 --> 43:33.360
Or...

43:37.573 --> 43:38.532
hot dogs?

43:40.534 --> 43:42.119
I'd have to say hot dogs.

43:42.536 --> 43:43.370
Great.

43:45.748 --> 43:47.249
[doorbell rings]

43:50.169 --> 43:51.045
I'll get it.

43:52.379 --> 43:53.297
[exhales]

44:01.180 --> 44:02.765
Hello there, neighbor.

44:02.848 --> 44:04.350
Uh, hi, um...

44:04.433 --> 44:05.351
-Martha.
-Martha.

44:05.434 --> 44:08.437
That's okay, Naomi.
I won't hold it against you. [laughs]

44:08.520 --> 44:12.441
Oh, my goodness. I love this little house.

44:12.524 --> 44:14.652
So nice to see it lived in again.

44:15.152 --> 44:18.864
I can't tell you how sad I was 
when I saw that "For Sale" sign go up.

44:19.406 --> 44:22.368
It's definitely a beautiful home.

44:23.243 --> 44:25.579
I'd feel awkward if I didn't tell you...

44:27.748 --> 44:29.708
We came to the open house yesterday.

44:30.542 --> 44:33.962
We just wanted to see the place
one last time

44:34.046 --> 44:36.674
before some stranger snatches it up.

44:37.174 --> 44:38.759
Oh, okay. Yeah...

44:38.842 --> 44:42.596
Oh, I almost forgot. 
I do that a lot these days.

44:42.680 --> 44:44.973
Uh... I brought you banana bread.

44:45.057 --> 44:47.685
You and Logan are gonna love it.
Everybody does.

44:47.768 --> 44:48.727
Thank you.

44:48.811 --> 44:51.021
Where is that handsome young boy?

44:51.105 --> 44:53.816
-Oh, he's in the kitchen.
-Oh.

44:53.899 --> 44:56.026
We're making dinner, so...

44:57.945 --> 44:58.821
Well...

44:59.321 --> 45:02.116
I just was gonna swing by 
and check in on you.

45:02.950 --> 45:05.577
If you need anything,
don't hesitate to come by.

45:05.661 --> 45:07.746
My husband can't wait
to meet the two of you.

45:10.457 --> 45:12.042
I'm sorry, um...

45:12.126 --> 45:13.293
but I thought...

45:13.961 --> 45:17.089
I thought you had said 
your husband passed away.

45:17.172 --> 45:18.465
Passed away?

45:20.008 --> 45:21.176
Oh.

45:21.260 --> 45:23.971
Why would I say something silly like that?

45:25.097 --> 45:27.975
No, no. The Devil himself
couldn't slow him down.

45:28.600 --> 45:29.893
You have yourself a good one.

45:31.729 --> 45:32.688
Buh-bye.

45:33.897 --> 45:34.940
Bye, Martha.

45:49.496 --> 45:50.539
[gasps]

45:50.914 --> 45:51.999
Shit.

45:54.918 --> 45:56.003
Ugh.

46:25.908 --> 46:26.867
[sighs]

47:09.535 --> 47:10.577
Logan!

47:39.690 --> 47:40.899
[clattering]

47:54.204 --> 47:55.372
[flashlight clicks off]

47:56.415 --> 47:59.209
[striking match]

48:01.044 --> 48:01.962
Oh, fuck.

48:02.045 --> 48:03.380
[matches clatter]

48:05.591 --> 48:09.511
[striking match]

48:13.849 --> 48:15.851
[striking match]

48:36.747 --> 48:38.040
[clock ticking]

49:09.655 --> 49:10.572
[exhales]

49:30.676 --> 49:31.635
[sighs]

49:48.944 --> 49:49.945
[urinating]

50:04.876 --> 50:06.086
[flushes toilet]

50:22.978 --> 50:24.855
[inhales, exhales]

50:41.288 --> 50:42.122
[grunts]

50:42.497 --> 50:44.583
[inhales]

50:44.666 --> 50:46.001
[exhales]

50:53.341 --> 50:55.177
Ally, I was married to a plumber
for 16 years.

50:55.260 --> 50:57.054
I think I know 
when a water heater is broken.

50:57.137 --> 50:58.388
[breathing heavily]

51:01.016 --> 51:01.975
Thank you.

51:05.854 --> 51:06.813
[sighs]

51:13.070 --> 51:14.529
[panting]

51:21.244 --> 51:22.162
[retching]

51:22.746 --> 51:24.039
[coughing]

51:24.122 --> 51:24.998
Logan?

51:26.083 --> 51:28.460
Logan, sweetheart. Are you okay?

51:30.420 --> 51:31.296
I'm fine.

51:31.379 --> 51:33.507
Oh, honey. Let me walk you home.

51:34.424 --> 51:35.884
No, no, that's all right.

51:35.967 --> 51:37.344
Nonsense. Come on.

51:38.470 --> 51:39.429
Come on.

51:46.978 --> 51:48.063
[grunts]

51:48.146 --> 51:49.564
Where did you come from?

51:49.648 --> 51:53.401
Oh, I always like to start my day
with a nice stroll through the forest.

51:54.277 --> 51:56.321
The nature... the air...

51:57.447 --> 51:59.074
How you liking the neighborhood?

52:01.785 --> 52:02.828
It's fine.

52:03.495 --> 52:06.206
Just hoping that the house sells soon
so that we can go home.

52:06.289 --> 52:08.708
[scoffs] You're not going anywhere
anytime soon.

52:09.084 --> 52:10.168
[chuckles]

52:10.252 --> 52:13.171
I'm sure of it. 
Houses up here take some time to sell.

52:21.638 --> 52:22.764
What happened?

52:23.431 --> 52:24.683
I'm-- I'm fine.

52:24.766 --> 52:27.060
Poor boy got sick on his run.

52:27.644 --> 52:29.855
But not to worry. I was watching on.

52:30.272 --> 52:32.566
-Are you okay, honey?
-[sighs] It was just a cramp.

52:32.649 --> 52:35.569
Nothing that a hot shower 
and a good breakfast can't fix.

52:35.986 --> 52:37.320
Well, thank you, Martha.

52:37.404 --> 52:38.655
I appreciate it.

52:38.738 --> 52:39.781
Hey, um...

52:40.574 --> 52:42.993
I hope you're both doing all right.

52:44.369 --> 52:45.245
Death...

52:46.788 --> 52:49.124
It's like it moves in and...

52:49.791 --> 52:51.042
never leaves.

52:55.046 --> 52:55.922
Buh-bye now.

53:03.889 --> 53:05.098
She's so weird.

53:05.640 --> 53:06.933
[engine turns over]

53:12.480 --> 53:13.982
[doorbell rings]

53:18.111 --> 53:19.487
I'm here for the water heater.

53:19.571 --> 53:22.324
-Great. Uh, it's just in the--
-In the basement, right?

53:22.824 --> 53:24.576
-Yeah.
-I've been here before.

53:27.746 --> 53:29.748
[presses key, "Rip Van Winkle" plays]

53:37.881 --> 53:38.882
[grunts]

53:45.472 --> 53:47.474
[turns faucet on, off]

54:14.084 --> 54:14.918
Ma'am?

54:15.001 --> 54:16.044
-Oh! Oh, my God!
-Sorry.

54:16.127 --> 54:18.505
Oh, shit. Sorry. Um...

54:18.588 --> 54:19.547
I didn't hear you.

54:20.882 --> 54:23.134
-How did it look down there?
-Normal.

54:23.218 --> 54:25.303
Relit the pilot. It's burning.

54:25.762 --> 54:28.890
Then I changed the thermal coupler. 
You should be good to go.

54:28.974 --> 54:29.808
Okay.

54:31.059 --> 54:33.311
-Wll, sorry for the inconvenience.
-No, not at all.

54:33.395 --> 54:34.813
I'm out here almost daily.

54:34.896 --> 54:37.857
This Martha down the road,
she lost her husband a few months back.

54:37.941 --> 54:39.985
She gets kind of sad.
I think she'd flood her house

54:40.068 --> 54:42.112
if it meant me stopping by
for a few hours.

54:43.321 --> 54:45.407
So, her husband did die.

54:45.490 --> 54:47.158
What, she told you something different?

54:47.742 --> 54:48.576
Yeah.

54:48.952 --> 54:49.869
Yeah.

54:50.495 --> 54:53.498
She got Alzheimer's a few months back,
so she gets things

54:53.581 --> 54:55.625
a little confused from time to time.

54:57.168 --> 54:58.378
-That's terrible.
-Yeah.

54:58.461 --> 55:00.505
Oh. And hey, I, uh...

55:00.588 --> 55:03.842
I found this by the water heater.

55:05.051 --> 55:06.720
Thought you might be looking for it.

55:08.930 --> 55:12.475
♪ I'm all right ♪

55:12.559 --> 55:13.852
[music stops]

55:15.645 --> 55:16.479
Found your phone.

55:18.898 --> 55:20.150
Okay. Well, where was it?

55:20.233 --> 55:22.652
In the basement next to the water heater.

55:25.196 --> 55:26.072
Oh.

55:26.656 --> 55:29.117
I must've left it down there
when I went to relight the pilot?

55:29.200 --> 55:31.536
Logan, your phone 
has been missing for days.

55:31.619 --> 55:33.913
You just went to check the pilot
last night.

55:35.457 --> 55:36.499
What's your point?

55:37.042 --> 55:38.710
And then I found this...

55:42.255 --> 55:43.548
in the trash.

55:52.849 --> 55:54.392
No. I didn't do that.

55:54.976 --> 55:56.770
Have you been messing with me?

55:56.853 --> 55:58.980
Have I been messing with you?
Are you kidding me?

55:59.064 --> 56:01.066
No, I'm not an idiot, Logan.

56:01.399 --> 56:04.611
First the basement door,
and then the water heater, and now this?

56:04.694 --> 56:05.653
What you talking about?

56:05.737 --> 56:07.989
Is it because you're pissed at me?
I don't know.

56:08.281 --> 56:12.452
Because I have so much on my plate 
right now that I can't deal with you too.

56:12.535 --> 56:14.996
I didn't do anything, Mom.
You're completely fucking insane.

56:15.080 --> 56:17.123
-Excuse me?
-Just get out of my room.

56:17.207 --> 56:19.125
-No. What'd you say?
-Get the fuck outta my room.

56:19.209 --> 56:22.545
No! You do not get to talk to me
like that. I am your mother,

56:22.629 --> 56:24.506
and I'm allowed to be upset.

56:26.216 --> 56:27.634
I know this sucks.

56:28.385 --> 56:31.096
I know it's not what you wanted,
'cause guess what?

56:31.179 --> 56:34.057
It's not what I wanted either.
So grow up, Logan.

56:36.935 --> 56:38.770
I fucking hate you.

56:39.813 --> 56:42.524
All you do is put your shit 
on other people.

56:42.607 --> 56:44.943
Dad's gone, and you don't even care.

56:45.026 --> 56:48.029
He died in front of me. You haven't 
asked me one time if I'm okay.

56:48.154 --> 56:50.532
You dragged me out of school,
brought us to this shitty town.

56:50.615 --> 56:51.991
You don't care if I'm okay with it.

56:52.075 --> 56:55.370
We wouldn't be in this situation
if Dad was still here.

56:59.874 --> 57:01.918
Wanna be an adult and know the truth?

57:03.086 --> 57:08.216
Your father is the exact reason 
that we are in this situation.

57:08.299 --> 57:11.302
Your father left us with nothing,

57:11.386 --> 57:12.929
because he was irresponsible,

57:13.012 --> 57:16.266
and he couldn't care less about me 
or about you!

57:18.268 --> 57:19.102
[inhales]

57:19.185 --> 57:20.520
I fucking wish it was you.

57:39.622 --> 57:40.957
[inhales]

57:41.958 --> 57:43.168
[exhales]

57:53.094 --> 57:54.095
[thudding]

57:57.474 --> 57:58.808
[clock ticking]

58:10.403 --> 58:11.237
Hello?

58:45.980 --> 58:47.148
[grinding noise]

59:07.627 --> 59:10.296
[grinding noise]

59:17.262 --> 59:18.096
Oh, my God.

59:20.056 --> 59:21.432
Hey, Dad!

59:21.766 --> 59:22.600
[groaning]

59:22.684 --> 59:24.227
No, no! Dad!

59:24.310 --> 59:25.979
-[gurgling]
-Dad! No!

59:26.062 --> 59:27.063
[panting]

59:27.146 --> 59:29.566
It's okay. It's just a nightmare.
You were having a nightmare.

59:29.691 --> 59:30.525
What?

59:35.321 --> 59:37.574
We have a showing in an hour,
so we gotta go.

59:40.076 --> 59:41.995
Wait a minute. What time is it?

59:42.078 --> 59:43.079
1:00 p.m.

59:43.663 --> 59:44.747
You slept all day.

59:52.297 --> 59:53.631
Logan, let's go!

59:57.385 --> 59:58.761
-Is your room clean?
-Yeah.

59:59.387 --> 1:00:01.347
-Where are you going?
-For a run.

1:00:11.524 --> 1:00:13.526
[breathing heavily]

1:00:35.340 --> 1:00:36.716
[gasps] Oh!

1:00:36.799 --> 1:00:38.009
-Hi.
-Oh, Naomi, uh...

1:00:38.092 --> 1:00:39.052
-Yeah, hi.
-Sorry.

1:00:39.135 --> 1:00:41.220
No, no. Um... you just startled me.

1:00:41.304 --> 1:00:43.264
Wow. I'm so glad I ran into you again.

1:00:43.348 --> 1:00:45.016
-How are you?
-Good.

1:00:45.099 --> 1:00:47.977
I'm, uh, just picking up some photos
I had developed.

1:00:48.061 --> 1:00:50.730
-Oh, are you a photographer?
-It's just a hobby.

1:00:51.272 --> 1:00:52.857
-That's great.
-Uh-huh.

1:00:58.863 --> 1:01:01.407
Hey, sorry I sort of disappeared 
on you last time.

1:01:01.491 --> 1:01:03.826
Couldn't find you. 
Figured I'd just get out of your hair.

1:01:04.410 --> 1:01:05.328
No worries.

1:01:08.831 --> 1:01:10.333
[Chris]  I know you don't know me.

1:01:10.416 --> 1:01:13.294
Last thing you need right now is
some guy scaring you in the parking lot

1:01:13.378 --> 1:01:15.129
and stalking your house. [chuckles]

1:01:15.963 --> 1:01:18.591
I just wanted to give you my number...

1:01:25.598 --> 1:01:27.475
in case you guys ever need anything.

1:01:28.601 --> 1:01:31.062
You know I just know
you guys are new around here.

1:01:31.938 --> 1:01:32.939
No pressure.

1:01:33.523 --> 1:01:34.565
Well, thank you.

1:01:34.649 --> 1:01:36.401
That's very sweet of you.

1:01:39.904 --> 1:01:41.197
[door creaks open]

1:01:56.170 --> 1:01:57.505
[cell phone chimes]

1:02:03.553 --> 1:02:05.847
Naomi, it's Allison.
We got a call from our realtor

1:02:05.930 --> 1:02:08.015
that our house was broken into.
Call me.

1:02:08.099 --> 1:02:09.392
Logan, get in the car.

1:02:10.184 --> 1:02:11.352
Get in the car.

1:02:24.407 --> 1:02:26.117
["Silent Night" playing]

1:02:27.827 --> 1:02:29.078
Oh, my God.

1:02:32.498 --> 1:02:33.374
Mom.

1:03:01.903 --> 1:03:03.905
[telephone rings]

1:03:09.368 --> 1:03:10.286
Hello?

1:03:11.788 --> 1:03:12.663
Hello?

1:03:17.627 --> 1:03:19.128
Mom, we have to call the cops.

1:03:21.798 --> 1:03:23.591
[indistinct police radio chatter]

1:03:27.303 --> 1:03:29.138
Ma'am, we searched the entire house.

1:03:29.222 --> 1:03:30.473
There's no one here.

1:03:30.556 --> 1:03:31.682
Did you check the basement?

1:03:31.766 --> 1:03:33.184
Yeah. Top to bottom.

1:03:33.768 --> 1:03:36.479
It's definitely creepy,
but we didn't see anything.

1:03:38.147 --> 1:03:39.023
Mom...

1:03:40.691 --> 1:03:43.486
Uh, well, we had an open house here
a few days ago,

1:03:43.569 --> 1:03:47.156
so maybe someone found 
a spare key laying around, or...

1:03:47.782 --> 1:03:49.116
Or maybe someone stayed.

1:03:53.287 --> 1:03:56.624
I know it sounds stupid, but other things
have happened before this.

1:03:56.707 --> 1:03:59.377
Things moving from one room to another.
Weird phone calls.

1:03:59.836 --> 1:04:01.087
From anyone in particular?

1:04:01.462 --> 1:04:03.381
No. No one would respond.

1:04:05.800 --> 1:04:07.468
Don't look at her. I'm not lying.

1:04:08.553 --> 1:04:09.387
Okay, look.

1:04:10.263 --> 1:04:13.391
I know that we probably sound
like the crazy new people in town,

1:04:13.474 --> 1:04:17.311
but this is my sister's house, and we're
supposed to be taking care of it, so--

1:04:17.395 --> 1:04:20.314
Look, I understand the fear
in these situations.

1:04:20.398 --> 1:04:21.524
Okay? I do.

1:04:21.983 --> 1:04:25.069
But it's likely the front door was
unlocked and some kids snuck in.

1:04:25.152 --> 1:04:26.529
Are you kidding me?

1:04:27.738 --> 1:04:29.490
Look at this. 
You think some kids did this?

1:04:29.574 --> 1:04:32.326
It's not uncommon. Okay?
Kids get bored. They do weird things.

1:04:32.410 --> 1:04:34.370
They were probably trying to scare
the newcomers.

1:04:38.040 --> 1:04:39.625
Okay. [clears throat]

1:04:40.501 --> 1:04:42.044
Is there nothing else you can do?

1:04:44.463 --> 1:04:47.049
If it makes you feel any better,
we can come by in the morning.

1:04:47.133 --> 1:04:49.302
Yeah. Yeah, please do.

1:04:51.262 --> 1:04:52.138
Okay.

1:04:52.680 --> 1:04:53.514
Let's go.

1:04:54.974 --> 1:04:56.225
You all have a good one.

1:04:58.686 --> 1:04:59.520
[door opns]

1:05:01.230 --> 1:05:02.607
-[Logan sighs]
-[door closes]

1:05:02.690 --> 1:05:03.649
[Naomi exhales]

1:05:06.694 --> 1:05:08.112
We have to stay in a hotel.

1:05:08.195 --> 1:05:09.655
Honey, we're fine.

1:05:09.739 --> 1:05:12.992
No, Mom. Something is clearly going on.

1:05:13.701 --> 1:05:16.203
Look, I know you think I did
all that shit before, but I didn't.

1:05:16.287 --> 1:05:19.874
-I swear to God.
-Okay. No, but you heard them.

1:05:19.957 --> 1:05:21.500
There's nothing to worry about.

1:05:21.584 --> 1:05:22.793
Mom, please.

1:05:22.877 --> 1:05:25.671
Logan, we can't afford it right now.

1:05:26.505 --> 1:05:27.340
Okay?

1:05:31.385 --> 1:05:32.428
We're fine.

1:06:13.678 --> 1:06:14.512
Hey.

1:06:19.850 --> 1:06:20.726
Mom...

1:06:22.019 --> 1:06:23.688
-I'm going to bed.
-Okay.

1:06:26.607 --> 1:06:27.525
You all right?

1:06:31.529 --> 1:06:32.530
Yeah, I'm fine.

1:06:35.408 --> 1:06:36.993
You wanna stay in here tonight?

1:06:43.499 --> 1:06:44.417
Sure.

1:07:00.725 --> 1:07:01.809
What is this?

1:07:02.977 --> 1:07:06.022
It's just the guy from the store.

1:07:08.190 --> 1:07:10.693
He gave it to me 
in case we ever needed anything.

1:07:11.193 --> 1:07:12.695
He was just being friendly.

1:07:13.279 --> 1:07:14.947
You can throw it out if you want.

1:07:16.240 --> 1:07:17.199
I don't care.

1:07:22.788 --> 1:07:24.040
I'm gonna go brush my teeth.

1:07:24.540 --> 1:07:25.374
Okay.

1:07:34.800 --> 1:07:36.177
[doorbell rings]

1:07:38.012 --> 1:07:39.472
[clock ticking]

1:07:44.185 --> 1:07:45.061
Logan?

1:07:47.438 --> 1:07:48.689
[doorbell rings]

1:08:05.998 --> 1:08:06.832
Hey.

1:08:07.833 --> 1:08:10.086
Chris. What are you doing here?

1:08:10.169 --> 1:08:11.337
[Logan] Uh, Mom.

1:08:11.420 --> 1:08:13.172
It's okay. I called him.

1:08:17.468 --> 1:08:19.470
The cops weren't worried at all, huh?

1:08:20.763 --> 1:08:21.597
No.

1:08:22.723 --> 1:08:26.102
-They said some kids probably did it.
-Well, that's possible.

1:08:26.727 --> 1:08:28.562
A lot of them are assholes up here.

1:08:31.941 --> 1:08:33.317
It didn't feel like kids.

1:08:36.403 --> 1:08:37.780
Oh, what did it feel like?

1:08:41.283 --> 1:08:42.159
Like...

1:08:43.577 --> 1:08:44.495
personal.

1:08:48.082 --> 1:08:49.792
Like someone had been here before.

1:08:52.253 --> 1:08:54.380
I don't know. Maybe I'm-- maybe I'm crazy.

1:08:59.009 --> 1:09:01.220
Well, it's just the two of you
up here, huh?

1:09:04.932 --> 1:09:05.808
Yeah.

1:09:20.447 --> 1:09:21.407
[locks door]

1:09:25.494 --> 1:09:26.579
Anything?

1:09:27.788 --> 1:09:28.664
All clear.

1:09:32.585 --> 1:09:33.460
Thank you.

1:09:34.128 --> 1:09:35.004
Yeah.

1:09:42.344 --> 1:09:43.804
-Hey.
-Oh.

1:09:44.889 --> 1:09:47.391
-Appreciate it.
-Yeah. Need anything else?

1:09:48.267 --> 1:09:49.768
Uh, no, I'm good, buddy.

1:09:50.394 --> 1:09:51.729
Yeah. Go get some rest.

1:09:53.856 --> 1:09:56.066
Hey, thank you for doing this.

1:09:57.610 --> 1:09:58.861
Yeah. Not a problem.

1:10:00.446 --> 1:10:02.656
Look, this place is weird sometimes.

1:10:03.324 --> 1:10:05.451
Yeah, it took me a while
to get used to it, too.

1:10:06.911 --> 1:10:08.579
I'm sure it's nothing, but, uh...

1:10:09.747 --> 1:10:10.664
I'll be here.

1:10:13.918 --> 1:10:15.294
I'm sorry, um...

1:10:16.212 --> 1:10:20.007
-if I was rude before. I just--
-No, no, no, no. No need to explain, man.

1:10:20.090 --> 1:10:21.175
We're all good.

1:10:23.219 --> 1:10:24.511
-Night.
-Night.

1:10:42.321 --> 1:10:43.530
[exhales]

1:10:56.252 --> 1:10:57.836
[thudding]

1:11:00.214 --> 1:11:02.841
[thudding, door creaks]

1:11:04.093 --> 1:11:05.302
[clock ticking]

1:11:11.016 --> 1:11:11.892
Chris?

1:11:21.860 --> 1:11:23.195
[engine turns over]

1:11:40.963 --> 1:11:41.839
Chris?

1:12:05.946 --> 1:12:07.197
Chris. Chris!

1:12:07.740 --> 1:12:08.574
Chris!

1:12:13.120 --> 1:12:13.954
[grunts]

1:12:45.361 --> 1:12:46.820
[panting]

1:13:51.051 --> 1:13:52.344
[exhales]

1:14:20.080 --> 1:14:21.331
[toilet flushes]

1:15:35.447 --> 1:15:36.490
Logan...

1:15:36.573 --> 1:15:37.908
[screaming]

1:15:43.372 --> 1:15:44.831
[choking]

1:15:50.837 --> 1:15:52.005
[Naomi groaning]

1:15:56.760 --> 1:15:57.970
[Naomi quivers]

1:16:04.268 --> 1:16:05.310
[Naomi exhales]

1:16:16.363 --> 1:16:17.281
[groans]

1:16:18.365 --> 1:16:19.449
No.

1:16:21.868 --> 1:16:22.786
No.

1:16:28.375 --> 1:16:29.251
Logan.

1:16:31.420 --> 1:16:32.379
Logan?

1:16:33.171 --> 1:16:34.339
[footsteps approaching]

1:16:34.423 --> 1:16:35.382
[gasps]

1:16:41.638 --> 1:16:43.265
No, no!

1:16:43.724 --> 1:16:44.850
No.

1:16:47.185 --> 1:16:49.396
Aah-- aah. Aah.

1:16:50.689 --> 1:16:52.774
[crying]

1:16:54.026 --> 1:16:55.944
No. Please, no.

1:16:56.778 --> 1:16:58.363
Please, no.

1:16:59.615 --> 1:17:00.824
Logan!

1:17:00.907 --> 1:17:01.742
[grunts]

1:17:01.825 --> 1:17:03.118
[coughing]

1:17:09.416 --> 1:17:10.792
[crying]

1:17:20.052 --> 1:17:21.345
[screams]

1:17:23.680 --> 1:17:24.890
[crying]

1:17:27.768 --> 1:17:28.852
[screams]

1:17:30.479 --> 1:17:32.105
No! No!

1:17:32.189 --> 1:17:34.191
[crying]

1:17:35.651 --> 1:17:37.861
[fingers crack, screaming and crying]

1:17:37.944 --> 1:17:39.279
[fingers crack, screams]

1:17:39.363 --> 1:17:40.447
[crying]

1:17:40.530 --> 1:17:41.573
[gasps]

1:17:41.657 --> 1:17:42.741
[shivering]

1:17:43.575 --> 1:17:45.577
No! [crying]

1:17:53.085 --> 1:17:54.044
[groans]

1:18:03.720 --> 1:18:04.596
Fuck.

1:18:06.932 --> 1:18:09.851
Logan!

1:18:19.736 --> 1:18:21.279
Hey, Mom! Mom!

1:18:22.572 --> 1:18:23.407
Mom?

1:18:32.708 --> 1:18:33.709
Mom!

1:18:34.584 --> 1:18:36.002
Mom, hey.

1:18:36.670 --> 1:18:38.672
Mom! Mom, what happened?

1:18:38.755 --> 1:18:40.424
-Look at me.
-Logan.

1:18:40.507 --> 1:18:41.967
-Here, get up.
-[Naomi cries]

1:18:42.050 --> 1:18:43.802
Get up. Come on.

1:18:44.761 --> 1:18:46.972
You're so cold. [crying]

1:18:47.055 --> 1:18:49.099
What did he do?
What did he do to you?

1:18:49.182 --> 1:18:51.351
I should have listened to you.

1:18:51.977 --> 1:18:52.978
Where's Chris?

1:18:53.937 --> 1:18:55.063
He's dead.

1:18:56.314 --> 1:18:58.316
What? Oh, my God.

1:19:00.652 --> 1:19:01.486
Oh, no.

1:19:01.945 --> 1:19:03.321
He's gonna come back.

1:19:03.613 --> 1:19:06.074
We have to get out.
We're gonna get out. Okay?

1:19:06.158 --> 1:19:07.284
Yeah, yeah.

1:19:07.951 --> 1:19:09.077
[Naomi whimpers]

1:19:09.161 --> 1:19:11.747
Look at me.
We're gonna call the cops.

1:19:11.830 --> 1:19:14.124
-I don't have a phone.
-I need to go downstairs, Mom.

1:19:14.207 --> 1:19:16.960
-No, baby. No!
-Hey, I'm gonna be fine.

1:19:17.043 --> 1:19:20.130
I'm gonna be fine, okay? I love you.

1:19:20.464 --> 1:19:21.423
Mom.

1:19:22.966 --> 1:19:24.176
I love you so much.

1:19:27.137 --> 1:19:28.597
I love you, baby.

1:19:36.855 --> 1:19:38.023
[Naomi cries]

1:19:56.124 --> 1:19:57.125
[ragged breathing]

1:20:14.059 --> 1:20:15.977
